==English==
===Etymology===
{{rfe|en|We need quality sources for these claims.}}
{{m|en||Yiff}} was part of a range of [[onomatopoeic]] words that form a [[pseudolanguage|pseudo-language]] used by the [[furry]] role-playing community: {{m|en||yiff}}, {{m|en|yip}}, {{m|en|yerf}}, {{m|en|yaff}}, {{m|en|yarf}}, {{m|en|growf}}{{,}} and {{m|en|growlf}} (in order from most positive connotations to most negative connotations). {{m|en||Yiff}} meant {{m|en|yes}} or an [[exuberant]] {{m|en|hello!}} Later, {{m|en||yiff}} was assigned a meaning of a [[sexual]] [[proposition]], a meaning that had previously been assigned to {{m|en|yipp}} (a coarse form of {{m|en|yip}}).  In modern use within the furry community, ''yiff'' almost exclusively refers either to sex between anthropomorphic animals, or pornographic depictions thereof.
===Pronunciation===
* {{a|GA}} {{enPR|yĭf}}, {{IPA|en|/jɪf/}}
